Jesse D. Garrabrant/NBAE via Getty Images . While teams have generally denied tanking this season, it became clearer that the phenomenon is real at the MIT Sloan Conference this past weekend when former Raptors GM Bryan Colangelo admitted his team tried to tank in 2012, Stan Van Gundy called this season's Sixers an embarrassment with Philadelphia GM Sam Hinkie in the crowd and Rockets GM Daryl Morey said things were getting ugly. "It's bad right now," Morey said. "I think last year, at the end of the season, I counted like two-thirds of the teams weren't trying to win." With six weeks left in this regular season, it could get worse. The Bucks, 76ers, Magic, Celtics, Lakers, Jazz and Kings are currently in a horse race for the best odds to get the No. 1 pick. Here's the latest Tank Rank: To read Chad Ford's latest edition of Tank Rank, sign up for Insider today. Insider Become an insider and get access to all our articles and tools. Subscribe Sign in View Insider Benefits Â» Magazine subscribers: activate your Insider account. Recommend0 Tweet0 Email Subscribe Chad FordSenior Writer, NBA Insider Follow Archive Senior NBA Writer for ESPN.com ESPN Insider NBA Draft Analyst since 2002 Writes ESPN's NBA Draft Top 100 and Lottery Mock Draft